        {"type":"faq","settings":{"question":"What does UV light reveal on a car's paint?","answer":"UV light reveals repainted panels, paint fading, body filler, rust forming under the surface, clear-coat damage, and moisture damage. These defects glow differently from original factory paint under UV, making them clearly visible in a darkened environment."}},
        {"type":"faq","settings":{"question":"How does UV light car paint inspection work?","answer":"A professional UV device is used in a darkened studio to illuminate the paint. Original factory paint has a uniform fluorescent response. Repainted areas, filler, and rust reflect UV differently — appearing as bright spots or dark patches invisible under normal daylight."}},
        {"type":"faq","settings":{"question":"Is UV paint inspection worth it before buying a used car in Pakistan?","answer":"Yes — UV paint inspection is the most reliable way to detect hidden accident history and repaint on used cars in Pakistan. Sellers rarely disclose repairs, and UV reveals what the eye cannot. The cost is a fraction of what you might overpay for a damaged car."}},
        {"type":"faq","settings":{"question":"How long does a UV paint inspection take?","answer":"A full UV paint inspection at Revive Auto Detailing Karachi takes 30 to 60 minutes depending on vehicle size. You receive a panel-by-panel paint condition report at the end."}},
        {"type":"faq","settings":{"question":"Can UV inspection detect repaint on just one panel?","answer":"Yes. UV light is accurate enough to detect single-panel repaints, even if the color match is visually perfect. The difference in UV fluorescence between factory paint and aftermarket paint is detectable regardless of color accuracy."}},
